               <p>THOMAS BATEMAN. I am a <rs id="t18280221-247-viclabel1315" type="occupation">bookseller</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280221-247-victim1414 t18280221-247-viclabel1315"></join>, and live in <placeName id="t18280221-247-crimeloc1316">Goodge-street, Tottenham-court-road</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18280221-247-crimeloc1316" type="placeName" value="Goodge-street, Tottenham-court-road"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18280221-247-crimeloc1316" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280221-247-off1313 t18280221-247-crimeloc1316"></join>. I lost a book on the 26th of January, but did not miss it till the officers told me of it; it had been inside my window, among some others, for several weeks; I am not certain when I had seen it, but I know it by the label.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280221-247-person1415">
                  WILLIAM 
                  JORDAN
               <interp inst="t18280221-247-person1415" type="surname" value="JORDAN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280221-247-person1415" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280221-247-person1415" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer. I saw the three prisoners together, in Leather-lane, that Saturday afternoon, about two o'clock; I watched them through several streets, to Gray's Inn-lane, where I met Cadby and Colton - we all followed them for five or six miles, through Camden-town and other places; when they got to Goodge-street, I saw Fowler take this book - the other two were close at his elbow; I told Colton and Cadby, who immediately ran across, and before I crossed they had got the three prisoners into a shop.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280221-247-person1416">
                  JOSEPH 
                  CADBY
               <interp inst="t18280221-247-person1416" type="surname" value="CADBY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280221-247-person1416" type="given" value="JOSEPH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280221-247-person1416" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was with Jordan, and followed the prisoners through a number of streets; I saw Fowler take the book, and the other two were close to him; I ran over and took Clark and Fowler into a linen-draper's shop.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280221-247-person1417">
                  WILLIAM 
                  COLTON
               <interp inst="t18280221-247-person1417" type="surname" value="COLTON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280221-247-person1417" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280221-247-person1417" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was following the prisoners - I saw Fowler take the book, and give it to Waghorn, who ran off with it, at the end of Goodge-street - I pursued and took him.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>CLARK'S Defence. I was looking for a situation - I saw Fowler, and asked if he knew whether it had gone five o'clock; before he could speak, the officers came, and pushed us into a shop.</p>
